<FORM ACTION="[% ip_search_url %]" METHOD=POST>
<b>IP SEARCH</b> Enter IP Address :
<INPUT type=text size=15 maxlength=15 name=ip value='[% ip %]'>
<br>Ignore clients who didn't log in during last <input type=text size=6 value=10 name=lastndays> days
<input type=submit value='Search for Email'>
</form>
<hr>
<b>Get accounts logged in with the same IPs</b>
<form action="[% ip_search_url %]" method="post">
<input type=text size=50 maxlength=50 name=loginid value='[% loginid %]' placeholder="user@binary.com"><br>
<input type=text size=15 maxlength=15 name=date_from placeholder="2016-01-01" value='[% date_from %]'>
<input type=text size=15 maxlength=15 name=date_to placeholder="2017-01-01" value='[% date_to %]'>
<input type="submit" value="Search for evidences">
</form>
With the help of this tool you can find all other accounts, who was logging into the system from the same IPs, that the stated user had.<br>
Can be useful in finding duplicates.
<br>
<hr>

[% IF logins.defined %]
[% IF logins %]
<b>Emails who has logged in in last [% days %] days from [% ip %]</b><br>
<table class="collapsed">
    [% FOREACH l IN logins %]
        <tr>
            <td>[% l.history_date %]</td>
            <td>[% l.action %]</td>
            <td>[% l.binary_user.email %]</td>
        </tr>
    [% END %]
</table>
[% ELSE %]
No logins found for IP address [% ip %] in the last [% days %] days
[% END %]
[% END %]

[% IF suspected_logins.defined %]
[% IF suspected_logins %]
<table class="collapsed">
[% FOREACH l IN suspected_logins %]
    <tr>
        <td>[% l.date %]</td>
        <td>
            [% FOREACH id IN l.logins %]
            [% id %]
            [% END %]
        </td>
    </tr>
[% END %]
</table>
[% ELSE %]
No clients have logged in from [% date_from %] to [% date_to %] from the same ips as [% loginid %]
[% END %]
[% END %]

